Project Overview
This project analyzes Wellmart retail sales data to understand store performance, seasonal trends, customer purchasing behavior, and the impact of external factors on sales.

The project demonstrates an end-to-end data analysis workflow, starting from data cleaning and statistical analysis to database management and interactive dashboard visualization.

Tools & Technologies Used

Python (Pandas, NumPy) – Data cleaning, preprocessing, and statistical analysis

SQL (MySQL) – Data storage and analytical queries

Excel – Initial data exploration and validation

Power BI – Interactive dashboard and visualization

Statistics – Descriptive statistics and correlation analysis

Project Workflow
1. Data Cleaning & Preparation (Python)

Loaded and cleaned the dataset using Pandas

Converted the Date column to datetime format

Created additional features such as:

Year

Month

Quarter

Removed inconsistencies and prepared the dataset for analysis

2. Statistical Analysis

Performed statistical analysis to understand sales distribution and variability:

Mean and Median to measure average sales

Standard Deviation to measure sales volatility

Coefficient of Variation (CV) to compare store stability

Correlation analysis to understand relationships between variables such as:

Fuel Price

CPI

Temperature

Unemployment

Weekly Sales

3. Database Integration (SQL)

Uploaded the cleaned dataset into MySQL

Performed SQL queries to analyze:

Store performance

Year-wise revenue trends

Seasonal sales patterns

Holiday impact on sales

4. Data Visualization (Power BI)

Created an interactive Power BI dashboard to present insights visually.

The dashboard includes:

Total Revenue KPI

Average Weekly Sales

Store Performance Analysis

Year-wise Revenue Comparison

Month-wise Sales Trends

Holiday vs Non-Holiday Sales Analysis

Interactive Filters (Year, Month, Store)

Key Business Insights

Store 20 generated the highest revenue (~301M), making it the top-performing store.

Store 33 generated the lowest revenue (~33M) over the three-year period.

2011 recorded the highest total revenue (~2448M).

2012 showed slightly lower revenue compared to previous years.

July recorded the highest monthly sales.

January had the lowest sales performance.

Holiday weeks show higher average sales compared to non-holiday weeks.
